                        <div id="page-title">
                            Forums : Fight Spam
                        </div>
                    

                    
                        <div id="breadcrumbs">
                            <a href="/start">W e l c o m e !</a> &raquo; <a href="/help">Help</a> &raquo; <a href="/howto:howto-list">List of community-edited How-To's</a> &raquo; <a href="/howtotopics:forums">Forums</a> &raquo; Forums : Fight Spam
                        </div>
                    

                    



                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<p><span style="font-size:smaller;">Posted by Phil Chett on <span class="odate time_1184926430 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%7Cagohover">20 Jul 2007 10:13</span>, last edited by Helmut_pdorf on <span class="odate time_1576752467 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%20at%20%25H%3A%25M%20%7Cagohover">19 Dec 2019 10:47</span></span></p>
<p><a class="wiki-standalone-button" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.editTags(event)">Tags</a>: <a href="/howto:_list-howtos/tag/block">block</a> <a href="/howto:_list-howtos/tag/delete">delete</a> <a href="/howto:_list-howtos/tag/forum">forum</a> <a href="/howto:_list-howtos/tag/move">move</a> <a href="/howto:_list-howtos/tag/post">post</a> <a href="/howto:_list-howtos/tag/spam">spam</a> <a href="/howto:_list-howtos/tag/thread">thread</a></p>
<div class="page-rate-widget-box"><span class="rate-points">rating:&nbsp;<span class="number prw54353">+3</span></span><span class="rateup btn btn-default"><a title="I like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, 1)">+</a></span><span class="cancel btn btn-default"><a title="Cancel my vote" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.cancelVote(event)">x</a></span></div>


<h2 id="toc0"><span>1. Block spammer</span></h2>
<p>The first thing to do, when some dear nice chappy (or chapess) starts playing silly buggers, is to block them.</p>
<p>At the moment, only admins can do this.<br />
This is done by going to <strong>site manager</strong>&#187; <strong>Security</strong>&#187; <strong>blocks</strong>&#187;<strong>User blocks</strong>.<br />
At the bottom of the page is <strong>+ add user to blocklist</strong>.</p>
<p>Enter the offending user name - than WAIT for answer of the system, showing all the found users with this name or starting with it (!) - and<br />
. select the correct user by mouse-click from the found list under the user-field;<br />
. enter a comment as to the reason for blocking the user.<br />
. click on button &quot;BLOCK&quot; !</p>
<p>Once that is done then there is the cleanup to be done.</p>
<h2 id="toc1"><span>2. Delete posts</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Rename the <strong>Thread</strong> to &quot;spam&quot;</li>
<li>Change the text in <strong>thread description</strong> to &quot;spam&quot; (using <em>edit title &amp; description</em> )</li>
<li>Delete the <strong>POST</strong>, and ONLY the <strong>POST</strong> &#8212;<strong>NOT</strong> the <strong>THREAD</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>(In this sequence!)</p>
<div style="font-size:150%;color:#F00;font-family:Comic Sans, Comic Sans MS,cursive;&quot;">
<p>Do not <strong>Delete</strong> the <strong>thread</strong> but <strong>MOVE</strong> the <strong>THREAD</strong></p>
</div>
<h2 id="toc2"><span>3. Move the thread</span></h2>
<p>(Using <em>move thread</em>) to the hidden category <strong>Hidden : per page discussions</strong> via the drop down list.</p>
<h3 id="toc3"><span>Note:</span></h3>
<p>Sometimes it takes awhile for the offending threads/posts to disappear from <strong>&quot;recent posts&quot;</strong> and <strong>&quot;recent threads&quot;</strong>.</p>
<p>Further reading: <a href="http://handbook.wikidot.com/en:block-anonymous-users-and-wikidot-members">Here</a></p>
<h2 id="toc4"><span>4. Post the spammer to Spambotdeathwall</span></h2>
<p>A good idea is to message the spammer to the community by posting it on <a href="http://spambotdeathwall.wikidot.com/" target="_blank">http://spambotdeathwall.wikidot.com/</a><br />
There is a spam filter tool running and sometimes someone will be able to message the ids ( site or spammer) to this tool.</p>
<p><strong>Authors</strong></p>
<p><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/phil-chett" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4297); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4297&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1586775511" alt="Phil Chett" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4297)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/phil-chett" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4297); return false;">Phil Chett</a></span>. <span style="font-size:smaller;">Please visit his/her <a href="/user:phil-chett">userPage</a>.</span></p>
<p><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/craig-macomber" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(28020); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=28020&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1586775511" alt="Craig Macomber" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=28020)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/craig-macomber" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(28020); return false;">Craig Macomber</a></span>. <span style="font-size:smaller;">Please visit his/her <a href="/user:craig-macomber">userPage</a>.</span></p>
